As you know, The Weekly Challenge, primarily focus on Perl and Raku. During the Week #018, we received solutions to “The Weekly Challenge - 018” by Orestis Zekai in Python. It was pleasant surprise to receive solutions in something other than Perl and Raku. Ever since regular team members also started contributing in other languages like Ada, APL, Awk, Basic, Bash, Bc, Befunge, Bourne Shell, BQN, Brainfuck, C3, C, CESIL, Chef, COBOL, Coconut, C Shell, C++, Clojure, Crystal, D, Dart, Elm, Erlang, Excel VBA, Fish, Forth, Fortran, Gembase, GNAT, Go, Haskell, Haxe, HTML, Idris, IO, J, Janet, Java, JavaScript, Kotlin, Lisp, Logo, Lua, M4, Macro Processor, Miranda, MMIX, Mumps, Myrddin, Nim, Nix, Node.js, Nuweb, OCaml, Odin, Ook, Pascal, PHP, Python, PostgreSQL, Postscript, Prolog, R, Rexx, Ruby, Rust, Scala, Scheme, Sed, Smalltalk, SQL, SVG, Swift, Tcl, Visual Basic, XSLT and Zig.
